        public boolean canAdd​(Coordinate c,
                      java.lang.String type)
        Tells if a given coordinate can be added to route. The condition is that the point must be in the map, the first point must be a stop and the the next must be directly connected with street.
        Specified by:
        canAdd in interface iRoute
        Parameters:
        c - is the point to be checked
        type - type of the point, "point" if regular coordinate "stop" if stop
